@description.name: @description
@description.body: Shows the blocker. When the show method is called a counter is incremented. The {@link #hide} method needs to be called as many times as the {@link #show} method. This behavior is useful, when you want to show a loading indicator.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Hides the blocker. The blocker is only hidden when the hide method is called as many times as the {@link #show} method.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Force the blocker to hide, even when the show counter is larger than zero.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Whether the blocker is shown or not.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Event handler. Called whenever the size of the blocker should be updated.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Event handler. Called when the scroll event occurs.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Registers all needed event listener.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Unregisters all needed event listener.
